Author: McARA
Vol / Page: 328
Edition:
Quote: Outcrop: The exposed portion of a reef, where it projects above the ground. The Martha Reef was the only one in the Martha Hill area which outcropped, the Royal coming in at No 4 level and the Edward at about No 5 level.  OED In Mining and Geol. The cropping out or emergence of a stratum or vein at the surface; or the edge of the stratum or vein that thus crops out [cf the second use, in the quot. above]
